abstract: Nevada won its coveted early date in the presidential primary because it was supposed to offer Democrats something different.
snippet: Nevada won its coveted early date in the presidential primary because it was supposed to offer Democrats something different.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Nevada won its coveted early date in the presidential primary because it was supposed to offer Democrats something different.
headline_main: Nevada Third to Vote, Still Up for Grabs for 2020 Democrats
headline_print_headline: Nevada Third to Vote, Still Up for Grabs for 2020 Democrats

abstract: A new report documents the concentration of cutting-edge industries in a few coastal areas and why lawmakers ought to be alarmed.
snippet: A new report documents the concentration of cutting-edge industries in a few coastal areas and why lawmakers ought to be alarmed.
lead_paragraph: There are about a dozen industries at the frontier of innovation. They include software and pharmaceuticals, semiconductors and data processing. Most of their workers have science or tech degrees. They invest heavily in research and development. While they account for only 3 percent of all jobs, they account for 6 percent of the country’s economic output.

abstract: While demanding that an opponent, Pete Buttigieg, disclose his McKinsey clients, Ms. Warren provided a fuller explanation of her compensation as a legal consultant.
snippet: While demanding that an opponent, Pete Buttigieg, disclose his McKinsey clients, Ms. Warren provided a fuller explanation of her compensation as a legal consultant.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren disclosed a detailed list of compensation she received during 30 years of moonlighting as a legal consultant — about $1.9 million in all — as she and Mayor Pete Buttigieg continued a back-and-forth demanding transparency in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination.

abstract: Rudy Giuliani didn’t get the job he expected. But as unpaid personal counsel to the president and for-profit peddler of access and advice, he got the spotlight.
snippet: Rudy Giuliani didn’t get the job he expected. But as unpaid personal counsel to the president and for-profit peddler of access and advice, he got the spotlight.
lead_paragraph: Not so long ago, it seemed to Rudolph W. Giuliani that he would be presiding over a hefty part of the world.

abstract: In 1919, John Maynard Keynes foresaw the chaos that would follow from the Versailles peace treaty.
snippet: In 1919, John Maynard Keynes foresaw the chaos that would follow from the Versailles peace treaty.
lead_paragraph: On Dec. 8, 1919, Macmillan Press published a book by a relatively obscure British Treasury official who had resigned from the government in protest over the Versailles treaty that brought the epochal trauma of the First World War to its conclusion.

abstract: Rob Sand figured out how to win statewide office as a Democrat in Iowa, and now the presidential contenders are seeking his counsel — that is, when he isn’t deer hunting with bow and arrow.
snippet: Rob Sand figured out how to win statewide office as a Democrat in Iowa, and now the presidential contenders are seeking his counsel — that is, when he isn’t deer hunting with bow and arrow.
lead_paragraph: CARROLL, Iowa — When I asked Rob Sand, the Iowa state auditor, if he could recommend fascinating Iowans to profile, he suggested himself. Then he suggested we go deer hunting.
